-- CNA Upgraded to BBB+ By Fitch on Insurer’s Reserves, Earnings
-- B y   M a r c i   J a c o b s
-- 2013-09-16T15:41:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-16/cna-upgraded-to-bbb-by-fitch-on-insurer-s-reserves-earnings.html
CNA Financial Corp., the commercial
insurer majority-owned by Loews Corp., was upgraded by  Fitch
Ratings  on improved reserves.  The issuer default rating was lifted to BBB+ from BBB on
“stable earnings, and overall good reserve quality,” Fitch said
today in a statement on Chicago-based CNA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marci Jacobs in New York at 
